ontinueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"e408f872-722a-4f79-90a3-eebc1524e821","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"ebc6e813-d624-42c8-b165-f409a3bd99d6","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"9b656252-31df-44d1-8a48-5c4b44937611","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5157,1420],"id":"9ab01773-7f5d-4053-b8ca-00cb14f80dd1","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#support","cachedResultName":"#support"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5481,1420],"id":"d4108f56-d442-42ea-affb-209921a20d15","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf10008-ticket`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Stamp & Shape Ticket","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"12bc7c5b-7a10-818b-d7d7-62ba1eb23dbc","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Ticket\n\nShapes the item: writes `ticketId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"b0bdb25f-4871-5c57-2c8a-5c8a86b2bf3a","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Ticket"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.ticketId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Detect Sentiment · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"f7626316-3b4c-d428-48a8-941fc91bf752","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"29ede048-8b30-00c2-fdc1-1fed052ecb0f","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Detect Sentiment\n\nScores the text's sentiment; ports fire positive / neutral / negative.\n\nPorts: ①→ Escalate Negative — Slack · ②→ Log Neutral Feedback, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Thank the Sender\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"fd1d83b6-8a89-c380-2399-b1487c923ab3","name":"Note: Detect Sentiment"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenRouter Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Detect Sentiment** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenRouter API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"b0f8e0c5-d58e-7279-8a4b-09e0705e3385","name":"Note: OpenRouter Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Negative — Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Open Zendesk Ticket · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,40],"id":"d90f2dff-2e94-6eec-b00f-424a4eee64ce","name":"Note: Escalate Negative — Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Open Zendesk Ticket\n\nzendesk — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Zendesk API token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,40],"id":"93f97b2e-32db-0660-7951-71815b1cda18","name":"Note: Open Zendesk Ticket"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Neutral Feedback\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,520],"id":"6a3faf82-d629-d8ec-52d8-b0dccc1ea763","name":"Note: Log Neutral Feedback"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Thank the Sender\n\ndiscord — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Discord webhook URL","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,1000],"id":"e555af98-ddd6-6b72-55dc-91d79014c78c","name":"Note: Thank the Sender"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Collect All Outcomes\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"764d2c67-d561-9898-e866-9779888d351b","name":"Note: Collect All Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"058b8d10-a04d-0a43-afbb-3c805728d0b5","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"c5a28d3e-b879-c229-a60f-476dffc7ff36","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Discord · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"d0831e01-b2e8-0f6e-079e-d9f77f588dba","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Discord\n\ndiscord — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Discord webhook URL","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"16ca95b4-8967-b9f7-5fcc-26ece6b6003f","name":"Note: Send Summary to Discord"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,1540],"id":"d501e63c-294d-95c1-c4f6-1b50548f2b4e","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,1540],"id":"f1bcdce3-c05f-84af-1e98-594234dc96b1","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Prioritize support tickets with Zendesk and Discord\n\n**Pattern:** Ticket Triage · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nPrioritize support tickets with Zendesk and Discord. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual auto-reply is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Stamp & Shape Ticket → Payload Valid? → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Slack → Open Zendesk Ticket → Collect All Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ticket triage without manual effort\n- Anyone automating auto-reply in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Responds in seconds\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Discord webhook URL; Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenRouter API key; Slack OAuth2; Zendesk API token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"a4c3dd30-c2fe-187f-f9a9-f6001cbded50","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"441d4724-f6b6-ed68-0290-3608110c0973","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"09fa56ae-978a-f1cd-ccfa-8c71f1c77ea0","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"e396b2ec-32d0-3375-1939-1fe1c480bb74","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your auto-reply process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"f427ba43-488e-d56e-7e80-83f2a83412c2","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Ticket","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Ticket":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenRouter Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Detect Sentiment":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Negative — Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Neutral Feedback","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Thank the Sender","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Negative — Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Open Zendesk Ticket","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Open Zendesk Ticket":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Neutral Feedback":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Thank the Sender":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Collect All Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Discord","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Discord":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"cd28758d-584d-4bdf-a837-434908b013bb","id":"FDX10008"}